{"type":"message","id":"951ea918","parentId":"bc2e00b1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:17:59.855Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the most recent pulse log and poll the pulse script.","thinkingSignature":"84dfc067b668dfce7f98e841ecfc4439afc0254ef75dc1774c03695f90cf9e8d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dfjc6iijmpqh_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 051622.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dfjc6iijmpqh_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"mild-lobster","timeout":55000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":422,"output":112,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12671,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774343875296}}
{"type":"message","id":"efc3896d","parentId":"951ea918","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:17:59.861Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dfjc6iijmpqh_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 051622\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. The key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n3. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on pulse logs\r\n4. Last pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 051530.md\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC classifier. This is a concrete next step.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what to do:\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe most concrete, actionable step right now would be to:\r\n1. Create a script or document that outlines the TIC experiment approach\r\n2. Or implement the TIC classifier itself\r\n\r\nGiven the \"file edits\" preference, I should create a concrete implementation file.\r\n\r\nThe most impactful single action would be to:\r\n- Create the TIC experiment script that will analyze the pulse logs\r\n- This sets up the infrastructure to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier for the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is solid - causal structure discovery and compression are the same problem. The TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate this hypothesis and advance Phase 1.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that will analyze pulse logs to test the hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure. This script will implement the core experiment to validate the duality.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$lookback = 20,           # Number of past pulses to analyze\r\n    [double]$threshold = 0.6        # Invariance threshold for classification\r\n)\r\n\r\n$logsDir = \"logs\"\r\n$invariantLog = \"research/tic_invariants.md\"\r\n$resultsLog = \"research/tic_results.md\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 1: Collect last N pulse logs ---\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem \"$logsDir/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First $lookback\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Analyzing $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 2: Extract structural patterns from each pulse ---\r\nfunction Extract-Patterns($content) {\r\n    $patterns = @{\r\n        goals = @()\r\n        actions = @()\r\n        files = @()\r\n        insights = @()\r\n        pending = @()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract ## Goals section patterns\r\n    if ($content -match '(?s)## Goals.*?(?=## |\\z)') {\r\n        $goalsBlock = $matches[0]\r\n        $patterns.goals = [regex]::Matches($goalsBlock, '- \\[ \\] (.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n        $patterns.pending = [regex]::Matches($goalsBlock, '- \\[x\\] (.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $patterns.files = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?:`([^`]+)`|(\\b(?:research|logs|state|scripts|config)/[^\\s]+\\.md)') | ForEach-Object { \r\n        if ($_.Groups[1].Success) { $_.Groups[1].Value } else { $_.Groups[2].Value } \r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action keywords\r\n    $actionWords = @('create', 'implement', 'write', 'update', 'edit', 'modify', 'define', 'measure', 'test', 'validate')\r\n    foreach ($word in $actionWords) {\r\n        if ($content -match $word) { $patterns.actions += $word }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insight patterns (lines starting with - insight or similar)\r\n    if ($content -match '(?i)insight[:\\s]+(.+)') {\r\n        $patterns.insights = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)insight[:\\s]+(.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Step 3: Build pattern sequence ---\r\n$sequence = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $patterns = Extract-Patterns $content\r\n    $sequence += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        timestamp = $file.BaseName -replace 'pulse_', ''\r\n        patterns = $patterns\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Step 4: Compute invariant patterns (appear across multiple pulses) ---\r\n$allGoals = @{}\r\n$allFiles = @{}\r\n$allActions = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($item in $sequence) {\r\n    foreach ($goal in $item.patterns.goals) {\r\n        if ($allGoals.ContainsKey($goal)) { $allGoals[$goal]++ } else { $allGoals[$goal] = 1 }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($file in $item.patterns.files) {\r\n        if ($allFiles.ContainsKey($file)) { $allFiles[$file]++ } else { $allFiles[$file] = 1 }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($action in $item.patterns.actions) {\r\n        if ($allActions.ContainsKey($action)) { $allActions[$action]++ } else { $allActions[$action] = 1\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:16:53\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343879861}}
